flowchart LR
    subgraph LEGEND[Legend]
        LU[Us]
        LC[Client]
        LM[MCP Server]
    end

    A[Browser opens dashboard] --> B[User clicks provider connect]
    B --> C[Backend auth connect endpoint]
    C --> D[Provider OAuth page]
    D --> E[Backend auth callback]
    E --> F[OAuthService stores access token]
    F --> G[Browser starts compliance run]

    G --> H[Backend API]
    H --> I[ComplianceController]
    I --> J[OAuthService getAccessToken]
    J --> K[Mapping stage]
    K --> L[ToolExecutionStrategy]
    L --> M{ToolResolver selects mode}

    A -. what it does .-> AX[User opens app in browser]
    B -. what it does .-> BX[Starts OAuth login for selected provider]
    C -. what it does .-> CX[Redirects user to provider authorization URL]
    D -. what it does .-> DX[User grants access at provider]
    E -. what it does .-> EX[Provider sends code and state to backend callback]
    F -. what it does .-> FX[Backend exchanges code and stores encrypted token]
    G -. what it does .-> GX[User submits standard provider repositories]
    H -. what it does .-> HX[Receives compliance evaluate request]
    I -. what it does .-> IX[Validates input and prepares controls]
    J -. what it does .-> JX[Loads stored token for tenant and provider]
    K -. what it does .-> KX[Resolves tool names and evaluation logic]
    L -. what it does .-> LX[Executes tool calls and gathers evidence]
    M -. decision logic .-> MX[Decision uses exposed MCP tools provider support and execution preference]

    M -->|MCP| N[Backend McpClient]
    N --> N1[Provider MCP URL]
    N1 --> N2[JSON RPC tools call]
    N2 --> N3{Provider}
    N3 -->|github| N4[GitHub MCP server]
    N3 -->|gitlab| N5[GitLab MCP server]
    N3 -->|bitbucket| N6[Bitbucket MCP server]
    N4 --> P0[Response conversion layer]
    N5 --> P0
    N6 --> P0

    N -. what it does .-> NX[Calls MCP endpoint with tool name arguments and bearer token]

    M -->|REST fallback| O[REST fallback client]
    O --> O1{Provider REST API}
    O1 -->|github| O2[GitHub REST API]
    O1 -->|gitlab| O3[GitLab REST API]
    O1 -->|bitbucket| O4[Bitbucket REST API]
    O2 --> P0
    O3 --> P0
    O4 --> P0

    O -. what it does .-> OX[Builds URL from REST contracts and calls provider API directly]
    P0 -. what it does .-> P0X[ToolExecutionStrategy normalizeEvidence with ResponseNormalizer]
    P0 --> P[Normalize evidence payload]
    P -. what it does .-> PX[Controller extracts common payload for evaluation]

    P --> Q[EvaluationEngine]
    Q --> R[ReportFormatter]
    R --> S[Backend response JSON]
    S --> T[Browser shows compliance report]

    Q -. what it does .-> QX[Applies control logic and produces pass fail metadata snapshot]
    R -. what it does .-> RX[Builds summary rows findings and report structure]
    S -. what it does .-> SX[Returns final compliance output]
    T -. what it does .-> TX[User sees table summary and reasons]

    classDef us fill:#e6f4ff,stroke:#1d4ed8,color:#0f172a,stroke-width:1.5px;
    classDef client fill:#fff7e6,stroke:#b45309,color:#111827,stroke-width:1.5px;
    classDef mcp fill:#e8fff2,stroke:#047857,color:#111827,stroke-width:1.5px;
    classDef neutral fill:#f8fafc,stroke:#64748b,color:#0f172a,stroke-width:1px;

    class A,B,C,E,F,G,H,I,J,K,L,M,N,N1,N2,O,P0,P,Q,R,S,T us;
    class D client;
    class N4,N5,N6 mcp;
    class N3,O1,O2,O3,O4 neutral;
    class AX,BX,CX,DX,EX,FX,GX,HX,IX,JX,KX,LX,MX,NX,OX,P0X,PX,QX,RX,SX,TX neutral;

    class LU us;
    class LC client;
    class LM mcp;
